  <Docs>
    <summary>Specifies a color override for a single entry in a font's CPAL color palette.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontPaletteOverride` lets you replace the color of a specific palette entry when cloning a typeface via <xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.Clone*>. Set `Index` to the zero-based index of the palette color to override and `Color` to the replacement ARGB color value.

## Examples

```csharp
var overrides = new SKFontPaletteOverride[]
{
    new SKFontPaletteOverride { Index = 0, Color = (uint)SKColors.Red }
};
var args = new SKFontArguments { PaletteIndex = 0, PaletteOverrides = overrides };
using var cloned = typeface.Clone(args);
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
